column4: Kaspersky files antitrust complaints against Microsoft in Europe
column5: Russian security software maker Kaspersky Lab has filed antitrust complaints against Microsoft with the European Commission and the German federal cartel office  it said in a statement on Tuesday.

column4: Early buyers of Tesla's Model 3 get two choices: color  wheel size
column5: SAN FRANCISCO Buyers of Tesla Inc's  upcoming Model 3 car will only get two choices in configuration  a policy that will let the company quickly ramp up production of its mass-market vehicle  Chief Executive Elon Musk told investors on Tuesday.

column4: Tesla shareholder vote against annual reelection of directors
column5: June 6 Tesla Inc said its investors approved all five of its proposals  including one that shot down a move to make its directors stand for reelection each year  at the company's annual shareholder meeting on Tuesday.
